I can play a few-- and these scales,
the basis of Indian classical music.

00:45:35.060 --> 00:45:37.740
So there are these 10 basic scales.

00:45:37.740 --> 00:45:41.380
We, at least in north Indian
music, we call them thaats.

00:45:41.380 --> 00:45:43.660
And then the thaats are--

00:45:43.660 --> 00:45:47.900
they're composed of like all
seven notes in the scale.

00:45:47.900 --> 00:45:51.690
And the raags when--
the ragas as created

00:45:51.690 --> 00:45:55.960
by picking certain notes
among the seven note scale

00:45:55.960 --> 00:46:00.660
and then creating some
patterns of movement so you--

00:46:00.660 --> 00:46:04.250
the ascending and descending
pattern differ.

